                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                <placeName>New Orleans</placeName>\n                <date>Oct 20 1853</date>\n            </p>\n            <p>\n                <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">\n                <placeName>Phila</placeName>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(3)\">Revd Sir</p>\n            <p>Pardon my long silence I am now<lb/> here again at your service &amp; will<lb/> drop\n                you a line whenever I find<lb/> anything worthy of note. The <persName>Revd<lb/> Mr\n                    Gutheim</persName> declining to continue<lb/> our Minister resign'd &amp; will\n                leave<lb/> us <date>January</date> when his term expires<lb/> We shall feel his\n                loss. We now<lb/> require one to fulfill his place<lb/> Salary $1500 &amp;\n                perquisites for Marriages &amp;c<lb/> We have no cheap ticher<add>?</add>\n                <add>?</add><lb/> Books the fine ones are not yet<lb/> sold. We have Elected our shomas<lb/>\n                <persName>Mr Goldman</persName> for Life at a salary of<lb/> $1000 &amp; 10% on\n                collections. His arduous<lb/> exertions &amp; good conduct are the reason<lb/> of\n                Increase of Salary. I recd $25. for<lb/> our congregation from <persName>Mr A\n                    Hart</persName><lb/> of your city over $3000 has been rec'd<lb/> by our\n                Congregation from various Cities<lb/> one Donation here of $500 was rec'd</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3d795x35/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
